## Assembling the Metagenome of Black Band Disease

Generating the metagenome of BBD from *Acropora hyacynthus* at Orpheus Island. Created a symbolic link between BBD data and raw_reads directory. Inside *flye* directory, modified a copy of run_flye.sh script (\> run_flye_bbd.sh) and submitted slurm to sbatch through:

``` bash
sbatch run_flye_bbd.sh
```

Step 2. Run metabat on flye_bbd assembly

``` bash
cd ~/MB5370_Module_03/metabat
# Extract depth information
cat ../flye/bbd/assembly_info.txt  | grep -v '#' | awk '{OFS="\t";print $1,$3}' > depths_bbd.txt
# Reorder contigs based on depth
cat depths_bbd.txt | awk '{print $1}' | xargs samtools faidx ../flye/bbd/assembly.fasta > assembly_bbd_ordered.fasta
# run metabat
metabat2 -i assembly_bbd_ordered.fasta -a depths_bbd.txt --cvExt -o bins_bbd/metabat --seed 5
```

Step 3. Run checkM on bins created by metabat. \*subsitute XX with nb of largest contig edge_121

``` bash
cd ~/MB5370_Module_03/checkm
mkdir bins_bbd
cp ../metabat/bins_bbd/*.fa bins_bbd/
samtools faidx ../flye/bbd/assembly.fasta contig_XX > bins_bbd/contig_XX.fa
```

Step 4. Create a new slurm shell script to send your checkM.

``` bash
run_checkm.bbd.sh

# Submit batch
sbatch run_checkm_bbd.sh
```

### Functonial Analysis of the BBD Metagenome

| Analysis Step | File/Folder                   |
|---------------|-------------------------------|
| Flye          | flye/bbd                      |
| MetaBAT       | metabat/bins_bbd              |
| CheckM        | checkm/checkm_results_bbd.txt |

Step 5: Bin checkm based on results

We isolated the bins with a completeness higher than 15% (into bbd_topbins.txt) using *cat.*


Step 6: Perform taxonomic classification with *gtdbtk*

We ran a classification workflow.


Step 7. Find and annotate genes with *prokka*

We identified the genes present within the genomes of bbd taxa.




